# Prisma Database Expert

Use when editing Prisma schema or reviewing Prisma usage in API services/repositories.

## Modeling / schema
- Normalize entities; avoid denormalization unless you have a clear read-path reason.
- Model relationships explicitly; use join tables for many-to-many.
- Prefer explicit `@relation` and clear naming.
- Minimize nullable fields unless domain truly allows absence.

## Queries
- Must use `select`/`include` intentionally to limit payload.
- Must avoid N+1; batch queries or use filtered relation queries where appropriate.
- Must paginate list endpoints (`skip`/`take` or cursor-based when appropriate).
- Must include tenant/company scope filters for tenant-owned data.
- Must prefer repository-layer query primitives over direct Prisma in services for high-risk domains.

## Performance / indexes
- Must consider indexes for tenant/company scoping + FK + fields used in `where`/`orderBy`.

## Migrations
- Must review generated SQL and validate with `prisma validate`; run risky migrations safely in non-production first.
